# Keep the build context lean AND keep secrets/local state out of image layers.
# Without this, `COPY . .` bakes the local .env (localhost DB URL, WATI token,
# CRON_SECRET) into the image and points the build's `prisma migrate deploy`
# at a database that isn't reachable from inside the container.

# Dependencies — reinstalled via `npm ci` in the deps stage
node_modules
.pnp
.pnp.js

# Build output — regenerated inside the image
.next
.next-prod
out
build
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo

# Secrets & local environment — never ship these.
# `.env.*` is what keeps the real .env.production (Supabase password, WATI token,
# CRON_SECRET) out of the image layers; the negations re-admit the value-less templates.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.supabase.example
!.env.production.example

# Supabase migration working dir — plaintext PII dump
.migration

# VCS & tooling
.git
.gitignore
.vscode
.idea

# Local scratch / captures not needed at build
.playwright-mcp
*.log

# Docker & compose files — not needed inside the image.
# NOTE: `Dockerfile` matches the ROOT one only, so docker/cron/Dockerfile and the
# sidecar's *.sh stay in the build context (the cron service needs them). Caddyfile
# is bind-mounted by compose rather than copied, so it is excluded too.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml
Caddyfile
